data.title: Waldemar, Prince of Denmark (1858
data.meta_description: Bust-length, in profile to the left, wearing the uniform of a Danish admiral, with the collar of the Order of the Elephant, stars and badges of the Orders of the Elephant and Dannebrog (Denmark), and badge of the Silver Jubilee of Christian IX.Waldemar, Prince of Denmark, third son of Christian IX, King of Denmark, and Louise, daughter of Landgrave William of Hesse-Cassel. The younger brother of Queen Alexandra, he married in 1885 Marie, elder daughter of Robert, duc de Chartres, by whom he had four sons...
